-- Virgin Media 2021 Noteholders Deny Consent for Changes to Terms
-- B y   J o h n   G l o v e r
-- 2013-02-15T16:09:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-15/virgin-media-2021-noteholders-deny-consent-for-changes-to-terms.html
Company received consents from “at
least a majority” of holders of 2018 and 2019 bonds to
amend/waive provisions of indentures: Businesswire statement
*Amendments will be operative only on successful conclusion of
planned merger with Liberty Global: statement
*Virgin to pay $5.00 cash per $1,000 notes held in two tranches.
First; 25% payment for waivers, then 75% for consent to
amendments: statement
*Consent period expired 5 p.m. in New York on Feb. 14; won’t be
extended: statement
